It's easy to see this cycle of wrath will perpetuate itself for hours and threaten to corrupt all, unless someone actively quenches it. It doesn't matter how small it started. Watching people lash out at each other one after another, one almost feels an evil force feeding off it.

If you try to keep an active awareness of it, it is very easy to see how minor sins escalate. Like at the start of a road trip someone forgets his water bottle and another person gets angry at having to wait for him to go back to pick it up, first one lashes out back at him, etc.

But one can also lose himself and add to the insults at another, or strike back with more vitriol if he perceives himself insulted. But that way he just perpetuates the cycle of wrath. The summer solstice is the most evil day of the year, full moon tonight, let us watch ourselves
